    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-15T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-15T09:00:00-05:00" n="420"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/253: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-15T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >July 15, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 15—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. My telegram of July 14, 2 p.m. I authorized the Consul General to approach
                    the Ministry of Marine with respect to the clearance of the steamers <hi
                        rend="italic">Delsud</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Angeles</hi>. Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_LST1">Lee</persName> reports that clearance was
                        granted—<hi rend="italic">Angeles</hi> without, <hi rend="italic"
                        >Delsud</hi> with cargo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
